title: For Sale:  Springfield SAR-4800 (FN FAL) - $2,250
postcontent:
Springfield SAR-4800 .308 semi-automatic battle rifle. After the early 90's ban, this was Springfield's sportorized version of the FN FAL. However, this one has a pistol grip stock set. The SAR 4800 was manufactured as a new rifle on licensed FN machinery by trained machinists according to specs with all IMBEL parts. Many franken-FAL's were cobbled together in a garage by a hobbyist. title: For Sale:  Saiga 12 ga converted semi-auto shotgun, w/ mods, 5 mags, and case!
postcontent:
I have a Saiga 12 shotgun (s/n: H09401715) that I am selling. I purchased this shotgun a couple of years ago and have done several mods to it over the time I have owned it. I did have to send it off to Saiga's stateside factory to have it worked on shortly after I purchased it, due to it not feeding low brass reliably (it would jam). This was done while under warranty, and after I received it back, it feeds low brass (i.e. birdshot) pretty reliably now (it will hiccup on a rare basis). It NEVER has any issues w/ normal brass (i.e. buckshot or slugs). I installed the "low brass reliability" kit from 
Carolina Shooters Supply, which included an after-market gas plug/puc and 4 position gas knob. This shotgun can handle 2 3/4" or 3" shells. 

I have also converted the trigger/pistol group back to where it was supposed to be (on the receiver). This SIGNIFICANTLY shortens the gun, as I found it WAY too long before. I put a Tapco 6-position collapsible stock with a nice, thick rubber butt pad on it. The stock features a cheek riser and a sling attachment for right handed shooters (see pictures). I added a nice rubber Hogue grip as well. I installed a Vepr 12 magazine release, which allows for one handed magazine release. I installed a JTE magazine guide (i.e. the "Rock-n-lock") to allow for quicker magazine changes when using the 10 or 12 round SGM Tactical magazines. I also put a Chaos extended quad rail on this Saiga, in addition to a Tromix extended charging handle (makes the charging handle MUCH more comfortable when charging with your left hand). I also polished the bolt to increase smoothness and reliability. This gun is SMOOTH... you can come shoot to test yourself. 

Last but not least, I put Magpul's flip up front and rear sights on this shotgun. I also have a cheap NC Star red dot which actually does hold it's zero even under the 12 ga recoil. Comes with a MidwayUSA soft case and five 10-round SGM Tactical magazines. Call if interested... I am not interested in any trades. I am asking $2200 obo and am listing this other places. These will be hard to come by in the future so I am not negotiating much at this point.  

I have plenty of pictures... they are too high quality to be allowed to be uploaded by armslist, so email if you want a link to view the album. Thanks for looking.

A battle rifle is only as reliable as its magazine – make sure the one in your rifle is from Brownells. When failure is not an option, these magazines deliver on the range, in the field, in a tactical situation, under fire. Load these smooth-feeding magazines to maximum capacity and fire the full 30 rounds you expect. No jams, no misfeeds, no hangups.

All components are made of mil-spec materials and are manufactured under strict, ISO quality control standards. The heat-treated, welded aluminum body is hard-anodized for superior corrosion resistance, then given a tough, dry-lube coating to eliminate the need for additional lubricants that would attract dust, sand, or dirt. The latest military-type, glass-fiber reinforced composite follower further guarantees flawless feeding in the harshest tactical conditions. Our new, high lubricity, dry-lube-coated chrome silicon spring that’s corrosion-resistant certified to 500 hour salt spray standards, and less prone to spring “set.” All models are available in standard military Gray.
